content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Sarl Dunegun

Sarl Dunegun was one of the Seven priestly warriors who died fighting the Morytanian hordes at Silvarea. He came from what is now Edgeville.

He is described in the Ancient tome as "A pious yet brutal man. When wielding his mace he led many fighters on skirmishes to keep the evil from spreading and outflanking the group."

The Ancient tome claims he hailed from Edgeville, a village that was not built until Year 169 of the Fifth Age, while Dunegun lived during the middle Fourth Age.

'''Sarl Dunegun''' was one of the [[Seven Priestly Warriors|Seven priestly warriors]] who died fighting the [[Morytania]]n hordes at [[Silvarea]]. He came from what is now [[Edgeville]].

He is described in the [[Ancient tome]] as "A pious yet brutal man. When wielding his mace he led many fighters on skirmishes to keep the evil from spreading and outflanking the group."

The Ancient tome claims he hailed from Edgeville, a village that was not built until Year 169 of the Fifth Age, while Dunegun lived during the middle Fourth Age.
